				\begin{document}$${{\rm{e}}}_{{\rm{u}}}={{\rm{L}}}_{{\rm{u}}}-{{\rm{L}}}_{0}/{{\rm{L}}}_{0}$$\end{document}eu=Lu−L0/L0where is Lu the final length of the outer arc and L0 is the length of the neutral surface. Considering that Lu = β r and L0 = β(r − h0), where β is the angle described by the arc of bending in radians and is equal to the dip of the lithosphere after the arc, h0 is the depth of the neutral surface and r is the curvature radius, the extension of the outer arc can be expressed by2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
